text: Zele () is a municipality located in the Belgian province of East Flanders, around 20 km east of Ghent. The municipality only comprises the town of Zele proper. On January 1, 2011, Zele had a total population of 21,333. The total area is 33.06 km2 which gives a population density of 645 inhabitants per km2. ==Famous inhabitants== *Basile De Loose, painter (1809–1885) *Pierre de Decker, former Prime Minister of Belgium (1855–1857) (1812–1891) *Aloïs de Beule, sculptor (1861–1935) *Filip De Wilde, professional football player (b. 1964) *Lieven Maesschalck, physiotherapist (b. 1964) *Christophe Impens, Belgian record holder 1500 m run, semi-finalist at Atlanta Olympics (b. 1969) *Caroline Maes, professional tennis player (b. 1982) *Vanessa Van Cartier, drag queen and winner of Drag Race Holland (b. 1979) ==References== ==External links== * *Official website Category:Municipalities of East Flanders
